<p>In terms of flights: The easiest is to fly into either Málaga or Seville airports (please check what is better for you). It would be great to meet on the Friday and Saturday for those of you who are still in Córdoba. Thereafter or before the wedding, there are some great spots to visit in and around Córdoba including some of the finest cities in Andalucía (Seville, Granada, Cádiz, Málaga to name a few).</p>

<p>Parking is notoriously difficult in Córdoba especially at that time of year. Therefore, for those of you that will enjoy a peaceful time travelling, the train system is great from either Malaga or Córdoba.</p>

<p>For those that are coming in from out of Europe flights, there are some decent transfers via Madrid, direct to Córdoba airport.</p>

<p>Renting a car is very straightforward. If you do so from Málaga, there is a website called www.doyouspain.com. Please though hire a car from inside the airport and not outside as it is problematic outside.</p>

<p>There are also coach options from either Málaga or Seville. For those of you that would like to take the train instead of road travel, this is how you can do it from Málaga, Madrid and Seville.</p>

<p>From Santa Justa train station, travellers can easily arrange onward travel to Córdoba.</p>

