			<p>For a reasonably priced method of reaching the train station in the city centre, there are regular Seville Airport buses operating between the airport and the train station in the city centre. The bus stop is on the far left from the terminal exit. The half hourly service operates between 06:15 and 23:00 every week day with fewer busses on Sundays.</p>

			<p>Seville Airport buses take approximately 20 to 30 minutes to reach the city centre, depending on how often they need to stop along the way. You can buy your bus ticket from the driver on the bus. The cost for a single bus journey is €2.40. The bus will drop you off just behind Seville Cathedral or at the central train station, if you prefer.</p>
